-- IMF's Board Should Have a Third African Representative, South Africa Says
-- B y   F r a n z   W i l d
-- 2010-11-09T07:04:23Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-09/imf-s-board-should-have-a-third-african-representative-south-africa-says.html
South African Finance Minister Pravin
Gordhan said Africa’s biggest economy will argue for a third
chair on the International Monetary Fund’s board for sub-Saharan
Africa.  Gordhan made the comments to reporters in Pretoria today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Franz Wild in Johannesburg at 
